## ğŸ—‚ï¸ Sample Table: `Students`

Imagine we have a table called `Students` with this data:

| StudentID | Name     | Age | Grade |
|-----------|----------|-----|-------|
| 1         | Alice    | 14  | 88    |
| 2         | Bob      | 15  | 92    |
| 3         | Charlie  | 13  | 75    |
| 4         | Diana    | 14  | 95    |
| 5         | Ethan    | 15  | 67    |

---

## ğŸ” Filtering Data

**Goal:** Show only students who are **14 years old**

```sql
SELECT * FROM Students
WHERE Age = 14;
```

ğŸ§¾ **Result:**

| StudentID | Name  | Age | Grade |
|-----------|-------|-----|-------|
| 1         | Alice | 14  | 88    |
| 4         | Diana | 14  | 95    |

---

## ğŸ”¢ Sorting Data

**Goal:** Show all students sorted by **Grade** in **descending** order (highest first)

```sql
SELECT * FROM Students
ORDER BY Grade DESC;
```

ğŸ§¾ **Result:**

| StudentID | Name    | Age | Grade |
|-----------|---------|-----|-------|
| 4         | Diana   | 14  | 95    |
| 2         | Bob     | 15  | 92    |
| 1         | Alice   | 14  | 88    |
| 3         | Charlie | 13  | 75    |
| 5         | Ethan   | 15  | 67    |

---

## ğŸ”ğŸ”¢ Filtering + Sorting Together

**Goal:** Show students who are **15 years old**, sorted by **Grade** (highest first)

```sql
SELECT * FROM Students
WHERE Age = 15
ORDER BY Grade DESC;
```

ğŸ§¾ **Result:**

| StudentID | Name | Age | Grade |
|-----------|------|-----|-------|
| 2         | Bob  | 15  | 92    |
| 5         | Ethan| 15  | 67    |

